http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/Education-conference/article13988971.ece

Azim Premji University is organising the fourth Philosophy of Education (PoE) conference from January 10 to 12 at the university. The objective of the conference is to bring together educationists and philosophers of education from across the world to discuss various issues that demand philosophical analysis. The conference will have talks by eminent speakers including Paul Standish, University of London, Jonardon Ganeri, University of New York, and Rajeev Bhargava, CSDS, New Delhi, on the themes, culture and school curriculum; Philosophy and the practice of teaching; Educational policy and philosophy of education, according to a release.